  "bib_entries": {
    "123539619": {
      "title": "Order expedition in multi-echelon production/distribution systems",
      "abstract": "In this paper we study a multi-echelon production/distribution system where the retail centers are allowed to replenish their inventory through a normal resupply channel or an expedited resupply channel by incurring an additional cost. An approximation scheme to find the operating characteristics of such systems is developed. The results of a numerical study indicate that significant cost savings can be achieved by using the policy suggested in this paper."
